    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong data-start=\"380\" data-end=\"396\">Shadow Lords</strong> are the tribe of dominion, strategy, and ruthless survival. Where other Garou charge headfirst into battle, the Shadow Lords win wars through <strong data-start=\"539\" data-end=\"550\">control</strong> — controlling information, fear, alliances, and the battlefield itself.</p><p data-start=\"624\" data-end=\"825\">A Shadow Lord believes the Apocalypse will not be stopped by honor alone. It will be stopped by the Garou willing to do what others won’t: <strong data-start=\"763\" data-end=\"825\">plan ahead, strike first, and sacrifice pride for victory.</strong></p><p data-start=\"827\" data-end=\"984\">They are the wolves who rule from the dark — tacticians, warlords, spies, and kings-without-thrones. They don’t need to be loved. They need to be <strong data-start=\"973\" data-end=\"983\">obeyed</strong>.</p><h3 data-start=\"986\" data-end=\"1006\">“Fear is not cruelty. Fear is clarity.”</h3><h2 data-start=\"2061\" data-end=\"2103\">What Shadow Lords Think of Other Tribes</h2><h3 data-start=\"2105\" data-end=\"2121\">Black Furies</h3><blockquote data-start=\"2122\" data-end=\"2183\"><p data-start=\"2124\" data-end=\"2183\">“They mistake rage for justice. It makes them predictable.”</p></blockquote><h3 data-start=\"2185\" data-end=\"2201\">Bone Gnawers</h3><blockquote data-start=\"2202\" data-end=\"2283\"><p data-start=\"2204\" data-end=\"2283\">“They see everything. That’s why we keep them close — and never let them lead.”</p></blockquote><h3 data-start=\"2285\" data-end=\"2305\">Children of Gaia</h3><blockquote data-start=\"2306\" data-end=\"2366\"><p data-start=\"2308\" data-end=\"2366\">“They want peace. The Wyrm wants extinction. Do the math.”</p></blockquote><h3 data-start=\"2368\" data-end=\"2378\">Fianna</h3><blockquote data-start=\"2379\" data-end=\"2459\"><p data-start=\"2381\" data-end=\"2459\">“They’ll sing as the world burns. Gods help you if they decide you’re family.”</p></blockquote><h3 data-start=\"2461\" data-end=\"2478\">Get of Fenris</h3><blockquote data-start=\"2479\" data-end=\"2541\"><p data-start=\"2481\" data-end=\"2541\">“A hammer is useful… until it decides everything is a nail.”</p></blockquote><h3 data-start=\"2543\" data-end=\"2560\">Glass Walkers</h3><blockquote data-start=\"2561\" data-end=\"2649\"><p data-start=\"2563\" data-end=\"2649\">“They’ll sell their soul to win a war.<br data-start=\"2601\" data-end=\"2604\" />We’ll just take their soul and win anyway.”</p></blockquote><h3 data-start=\"2651\" data-end=\"2665\">Red Talons</h3><blockquote data-start=\"2666\" data-end=\"2701\"><p data-start=\"2668\" data-end=\"2701\">“Pure predators. Pure stupidity.”</p></blockquote><h3 data-start=\"2703\" data-end=\"2722\">Silent Striders</h3><blockquote data-start=\"2723\" data-end=\"2772\"><p data-start=\"2725\" data-end=\"2772\">“They carry secrets like bones in their teeth.”</p></blockquote><h3 data-start=\"2774\" data-end=\"2790\">Silver Fangs</h3><blockquote data-start=\"2791\" data-end=\"2865\"><p data-start=\"2793\" data-end=\"2865\">“They think birth makes them kings. We think kings should be competent.”</p></blockquote><h3 data-start=\"2867\" data-end=\"2881\">Stargazers</h3><blockquote data-start=\"2882\" data-end=\"2936\"><p data-start=\"2884\" data-end=\"2936\">“They call hesitation ‘wisdom.’ I call it weakness.”</p></blockquote><h3 data-start=\"2938\" data-end=\"2948\">Uktena</h3><blockquote data-start=\"2949\" data-end=\"3011\"><p data-start=\"2951\" data-end=\"3011\">“Never threaten an Uktena. You will not see what kills you.”</p></blockquote><h3 data-start=\"3013\" data-end=\"3024\">Wendigo</h3><blockquote data-start=\"3025\" data-end=\"3085\"><p data-start=\"3027\" data-end=\"3085\">“They remember every betrayal. That makes them dangerous.”</p></blockquote>",
